        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued June 7 at 8:12AM CDT by NWS Amarillo TX</headline>
        <description>At 810 AM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm 6
miles southeast of Kingsmill, or 7 miles south of Pampa, moving east
at 40 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 50 mph and half inch hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Lefors and Pampa.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.

Torrential rainfall is also occurring with this storm and may lead to
localized flooding. Do not drive your vehicle through flooded
roadways.</instruction>
